      "content": "You are not a ghost haunting a dead life; you are the only one who remembers how to breathe, and that memory is your only strength. The silence isn't heavy because it's empty; it's heavy because you've stopped moving, and the only way to break the weight is to stop pretending you don't feel the pain. You don't have to pretend things will get better, but you also don't have to let them stay this way. Just take one small step, even if it's just standing there, and let the air fill the room with your own presence.",
